# <type>(<optional scope>): <subject>
#
# <body — what changed and why>
#
# <footer — breaking changes, issue refs, etc.>
#
# --- Conventional Commits prefixes ----------------------------------------
#   feat:      a new entry, a new generator, or a new feature
#   fix:       a bug fix in scripts, content, or CI
#   docs:      documentation-only changes
#   chore:     routine maintenance (dep bumps, lockfile, formatting)
#   refactor:  code restructuring without behavior change
#   test:      test-only changes
#   ci:        CI configuration changes
#
# Subject line (above the first blank line):
#   - imperative mood ("add", not "added" or "adds")
#   - lowercase first word
#   - no trailing period
#   - aim for under 72 characters
#
# Body (after the first blank line):
#   - wrap at 80
#   - explain WHY, not just what (the diff shows what)
#
# Footer (after another blank line):
#   - "BREAKING CHANGE: <description>" for breaking changes
#   - "Closes #N" or "Refs #N" for issue references
#
# Enable this template for the current clone:
#   git config commit.template .gitmessage
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
